results.name: Number of non-unitary prime divisors of Catalan numbers, i.e., number of those prime factors whose exponent is greater than one.
link: Michael De Vlieger, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: Table[Boole[n == 1] + PrimeNu@ # - Count[Transpose[FactorInteger@ #][[2]], 1] &@ CatalanNumber@ n, {n, 105}] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Feb 25 2017, after _Harvey P. Dale_ at A056169 *)
